Reasoning: The paper discusses formal modeling and analysis of temporal features in computer-based systems, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The focus on formalisms and models suggests that cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is a likely category. The mention of real-time and embedded systems, as well as hybrid systems control, suggests cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.PL (Programming Languages) as likely categories. The discussion of biological and social systems modeling suggests cs.SY (Systems and Control) as a possible category. Finally, the mention of pervasive computing suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as a possible category.
